<h2 data-start="687" data-end="752"><strong data-start="687" data-end="752">Hampta Pass or Valley of Flowers Trek – Book Now for 10% Off!</strong></h2>
<p class="" data-start="266" data-end="706">"Picture this — you’re standing at a crossroads in the Himalayas, and two amazing trails lie before you. On one side, there’s the adventurous <strong>Hampta Pass trek</strong>, with its rugged terrain, snowy patches, and breathtaking views that make your heart race. On the other, the <strong>Valley of Flowers Trek</strong>, a magical carpet of vibrant blooms and serene meadows that feels like stepping into a dream. So, which one should you pick? Well, why choose at all?</p>
<p class="" data-start="708" data-end="1070">This 2025 trekking season, you can experience the best of both worlds — the thrill of <strong>Hampta Pass and the tranquility of the Valley of Flowers</strong>. And here’s the kicker: you can book either trek now with a <strong>whopping 10% discount!</strong> Whether you’re a seasoned trekker hungry for adventure or a nature lover seeking peace, these treks promise memories to last a lifetime.</p>
<p class="" data-start="1072" data-end="1303">So, take a deep breath, let the mountains call you, and grab this chance to explore two of India’s most stunning Himalayan treks — without burning a hole in your pocket. The Himalayas are waiting. Are you ready to answer the call?"</p>

<h2 class="" data-start="975" data-end="1036"><strong>Hampta Pass Trek – Where Two Worlds Collide</strong></h2>
<ul>
 	<li data-start="1084" data-end="1114"><strong data-start="1084" data-end="1095">Region:</strong> Himachal Pradesh</li>
 	<li data-start="1084" data-end="1114"><strong data-start="1117" data-end="1130">Altitude:</strong> 14,107 ft</li>
 	<li data-start="1084" data-end="1114"><strong data-start="1145" data-end="1158">Duration:</strong> 4–5 Days</li>
 	<li data-start="1084" data-end="1114"><strong data-start="1172" data-end="1187">Difficulty:</strong> Moderate</li>
 	<li data-start="1084" data-end="1114"><strong data-start="1201" data-end="1220">Original Price:</strong> ₹7,500</li>
 	<li data-start="1084" data-end="1114"><strong data-start="1232" data-end="1253">Discounted Price:</strong> ₹6,750</li>
</ul>
<p class="" data-start="213" data-end="483">"Friends, imagine starting your trek in the lush green valleys of Kullu — pine forests, wildflowers, and fresh mountain air. But as you climb higher, nature flips the page. Suddenly, you’re in Spiti — a cold desert with barren cliffs, snow patches, and dramatic silence.</p>
<p class="" data-start="485" data-end="552">Yes, this is <a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/hampta-pass-trek/"><strong>Hampta Pass Trek</strong> — <strong>where two worlds literally collide</strong>.</a></p>
<p class="" data-start="554" data-end="672">In just 4–5 days, you walk from forests to glaciers, rivers to rocky passes, green to grey — beauty to raw wilderness.</p>
<p class="" data-start="674" data-end="838">If you want a trek that surprises you at every turn, where the Himalayas show you both softness and strength, then <a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/hampta-pass-trek/"><strong>Hampta Pass</strong></a> is the adventure you’re looking for."</p>
<p class="" data-start="1529" data-end="1562"><strong data-start="1529" data-end="1543">Best Time:</strong> June to early July</p>
<h2 class="" data-start="1569" data-end="1626"><strong>Valley of Flowers Trek – A Sacred Floral Wonderland</strong></h2>
<ul>
 	<li data-start="1630" data-end="1655"><strong data-start="1630" data-end="1641">Region:</strong> Uttarakhand</li>
 	<li data-start="1630" data-end="1655"><strong data-start="1658" data-end="1671">Altitude:</strong> 12,140 ft</li>
 	<li data-start="1630" data-end="1655"><strong data-start="1686" data-end="1699">Duration:</strong> 5–6 Days</li>
 	<li data-start="1630" data-end="1655"><strong data-start="1713" data-end="1728">Difficulty:</strong> Easy to Moderate</li>
 	<li data-start="1630" data-end="1655"><strong data-start="1750" data-end="1769">Original Price:</strong> ₹9,000</li>
 	<li data-start="1630" data-end="1655"><strong data-start="1781" data-end="1802">Discounted Price:</strong> ₹8,100</li>
</ul>
<p class="" data-start="221" data-end="518">Take a moment. Breathe in. Now imagine this — a valley so full of colors that even your dreams feel dull in comparison. Over 500 types of Himalayan flowers blooming together like nature’s own festival. Snow-covered peaks watching over, and soft clouds floating low like blessings from the sky.</p>
<p class="" data-start="520" data-end="581">This is not fantasy — this is the <a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/valley-of-flowers-trek/"><strong data-start="554" data-end="580">Valley of Flowers Trek</strong></a>.</p>
<p class="" data-start="583" data-end="804">Every step here is sacred. With every breath, you feel nature healing you. This trek isn’t just about walking — it’s about feeling, believing, and connecting. It’s where mythology meets magic, and nature speaks in colors.</p>
