<h2 data-start="3324" data-end="3368"><strong>FAQ</strong></h2>
<h4 class="" data-start="314" data-end="398"><strong>Q: Which is better for first-time trekkers: Hampta Pass or Valley of Flowers?</strong></h4>
<p class="" data-start="400" data-end="614"><strong data-start="400" data-end="406">A:</strong> The Valley of Flowers trek is more beginner-friendly with a well-defined trail and gradual ascent. Hampta Pass is moderate in difficulty and better suited for trekkers with some experience or decent fitness.</p>

<h4 class="" data-start="621" data-end="674"><strong>Q: Is acclimatization required for both treks?</strong></h4>
<p class="" data-start="676" data-end="897"><strong data-start="676" data-end="682">A:</strong> Yes, both treks reach altitudes above 12,140 ft. It's important to stay hydrated and allow a day for acclimatization, especially before Hemkund Sahib (on the Valley of Flowers route) or the pass crossing on Hampta.</p>

<h4 class="" data-start="904" data-end="981"><strong>Q: What are the best months to trek Hampta Pass and Valley of Flowers?</strong></h4>
<p class="" data-start="983" data-end="991"><strong data-start="983" data-end="989">A:&nbsp; </strong><strong data-start="994" data-end="1010">Hampta Pass:</strong> June to early July and September</p>
<p class="" data-start="983" data-end="991"><strong data-start="1048" data-end="1070">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Valley of Flowers:</strong> Mid-July to late August, when the flowers are in full bloom.</p>

<h4 class="" data-start="1138" data-end="1185"><strong>&nbsp;Q: Are permits required for these treks?</strong></h4>
<p class="" data-start="1187" data-end="1237"><strong data-start="1187" data-end="1193">A:</strong> Yes. Both treks fall under protected zones:</p>

<ul data-start="1238" data-end="1429">
 	<li class="" data-start="1238" data-end="1322">
<p class="" data-start="1240" data-end="1322"><strong data-start="1240" data-end="1256">Hampta Pass:</strong> Forest permits are required and arranged by your trekking agency.</p>
</li>
 	<li class="" data-start="1323" data-end="1429">
<p class="" data-start="1325" data-end="1429"><strong data-start="1325" data-end="1347">Valley of Flowers:</strong> Entry permits are mandatory for the national park, available at the base village.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h4 class="" data-start="1436" data-end="1476"><strong>Q: Can I see snow on either trek?</strong></h4>
<p class="" data-start="1478" data-end="1628"><strong data-start="1478" data-end="1484">A:</strong> Yes! On <strong data-start="1493" data-end="1508">Hampta Pass</strong>, you'll cross snow patches even in June. <strong data-start="1550" data-end="1571">Valley of Flowers</strong> may have residual snow near Hemkund Sahib in early July.</p>

<h4 class="" data-start="1635" data-end="1671"><strong>Q: Which trek is more scenic?</strong></h4>
<p class="" data-start="1673" data-end="1892"><strong data-start="1673" data-end="1679">A:</strong> Both are stunning in their own way. Hampta offers dramatic terrain shifts — lush greenery to desert-like Spiti. Valley of Flowers provides a fairy-tale experience with colorful meadows and spiritual surroundings.</p>

<h4 class="" data-start="1899" data-end="1962"><strong>Q: Is the 10% discount available for group bookings too?</strong></h4>
<p class="" data-start="1964" data-end="2147"><strong data-start="1964" data-end="1970">A:</strong> Yes! The 10% off applies to <strong data-start="1999" data-end="2007">solo</strong> and <strong data-start="2012" data-end="2030">group bookings</strong> made before the offer deadline. Group discounts may include additional perks — contact us directly for group quotes.</p>

<h4 class="" data-start="2154" data-end="2212"><strong>Q: What’s included in the ₹6,750 and ₹8,100 prices?</strong></h4>
<p class="" data-start="2214" data-end="2252"><strong data-start="2214" data-end="2220">A:</strong> These discounted rates include:</p>

<ul data-start="2253" data-end="2435">
 	<li class="" data-start="2253" data-end="2283">
<p class="" data-start="2255" data-end="2283">Guide and trek leader fees</p>
</li>
 	<li class="" data-start="2284" data-end="2302">
<p class="" data-start="2286" data-end="2302">Forest permits</p>
</li>
 	<li class="" data-start="2303" data-end="2340">
<p class="" data-start="2305" data-end="2340">Accommodation (tents/guesthouses)</p>
</li>
 	<li class="" data-start="2341" data-end="2366">
<p class="" data-start="2343" data-end="2366">Meals during the trek</p>
</li>
 	<li class="" data-start="2367" data-end="2435">
<p class="" data-start="2369" data-end="2435">Transport from base camp (as per itinerary)</p>
</li>
 	<li class="" data-start="2367" data-end="2435">
